OL,3,CConman took thousands from pensioners
OL,4,Cfor work he never intended to do
OL,6,FFrancis proceeded to say he had
OL,7,Finjured his thumb and could not do the
OL,8,Fwork at that time.
OL,10,FThe final victim, a 78-year-old woman,
OL,11,Fpaid Francis #166 for guttering and
OL,12,Fother manual jobs. The defendant then
OL,13,Fleft a note claiming he needed an
OL,14,Fadditional #200.
OL,16,FHowever, when he returned to collect
OL,17,Fthe cash, he was met at the door by
OL,18,Fthe woman's son who confronted
OL,19,FFrancis, and detained him with the
OL,20,Fhelp of neighbours, until the police
OL,21,Farrived.
