OL,3,CConman took thousands from pensioners
OL,4,Cfor work he never intended to do
OL,6,FJon Tarrant, defending Francis, said
OL,7,Fthat at the time of the incidents, his
OL,8,Fclient was "mired in problems with
OL,9,Falcohol and cocaine".
OL,11,FHe said his client has been sober for
OL,12,F143 days and recognises in his
OL,13,Fsobriety how "selfish and mean" his
OL,14,Factions were. He added that his client
OL,15,Fis extremely remorseful.
OL,17,FJudge Paul Thomas KC told the
OL,18,Fdefendant he had taken advantage of
OL,19,Fthree vulnerable people in a
OL,20,F"despicable" series of offences.
